      "content": "The emptiness you feel is the echo of a life that was completely defined by someone else, and that loss is profound. When everything feels pointless, it's because the anchor of your world has been pulled away, and that is agonizing. If the shell is all that remains, perhaps the smallest act of self-reclamation—a tiny, selfish thing—is the only thing left to focus on. You deserve a space where your own existence doesn't feel like a burden.",
